Package fr.univartois.cril.approximation.util.collections.heaps

Class Heap<E>

java.lang.Object
java.util.AbstractCollection<E>
fr.univartois.cril.approximation.util.collections.heaps.Heap<E>
Type Parameters:
E - The type of the elements in the heap.
All Implemented Interfaces:
Iterable<E>, Collection<E>, Queue<E>
public final class Heap<E> extends AbstractCollection<E> implements Queue<E>
The Heap is an implementation of a heap allowing to retrieve any of its element efficiently, thanks to index functions. The value of an element in the heap can also be updated, so that the heap remains consistent even if updated values alter the order of the elements, providing that the heap is told about this update by using increase(Object) or decrease(Object).
